narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Not much work. If you like game theory, take it, but be prepared to sit through some boring stuff. The final was also way too hard.
I would recommend it for someone who has not taken Game Theory before. I spent a lot of time doing problems I already knew how to do.
I would recommend this class to another student. Great class and not too difficult.

The first part of the course focuses on a general introduction to game theory whereas the second half of the course focuses on voting, election, and government accountability models. I would recommend it to another student if they have taken a previous course on game theory because I think it would be a good way in which to build off of that previous knowledge.
